   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🔤 Week 2 Hacker Track — Character-Level Name Completer\n",
    "### WnCC Machine Learning Learner Space 2026\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "You will build a **character-level language model** from scratch using NumPy.\n",
    "\n",
    "Given the first few characters of a name, it will predict the next character — and by sampling repeatedly, complete the name.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Input:  D, h, r\n",
    "Model:  → u (most likely next char)\n",
    "         → D, h, r, u\n",
    "Model:  → v\n",
    "         → D, h, r, u, v\n",
    "Model:  → <END>\n",
    "Output: Dhruv\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**This is literally a miniature GPT.** The architecture is:\n",
    "```\n",
    "Character → One-Hot → Embedding Lookup → MLP → Softmax over next characters\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Inspiration:** Andrej Karpathy's [makemore](https://github.com/karpathy/makemore). If you finish this, watch his video series — it builds directly on this concept all the way to transformers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# ========== SETUP ==========\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import random\n",
    "\n",
    "# Indian names dataset (a subset — you can add more!)\n",
    "NAMES = [\n",
    "    'aarav', 'aanya', 'aditya', 'ananya', 'arjun', 'aryan', 'avni', 'ayaan',\n",
    "    'bhavya', 'chetan', 'darsh', 'deepa', 'devika', 'dhriti', 'dhruv', 'divya',\n",
    "    'esha', 'farhan', 'gaurav', 'geeta', 'harsh', 'isha', 'ishaan', 'jatin',\n",
    "    'kavya', 'kiran', 'kirti', 'krishna', 'kunal', 'lakshmi', 'lavanya', 'madhav',\n",
    "    'manav', 'mansi', 'meera', 'mihir', 'mohit', 'naina', 'nakul', 'neha',\n",
    "    'nikhil', 'nikita', 'nilesh', 'nisha', 'om', 'pankaj', 'parth', 'pooja',\n",
    "    'prachi', 'pranav', 'priya', 'rahul', 'raj', 'rajesh', 'rakesh', 'ram',\n",
    "    'ravi', 'reena', 'rhea', 'riya', 'rohan', 'rohit', 'ruhi', 'sachin',\n",
    "    'sahil', 'samarth', 'sana', 'sanaya', 'sanya', 'sarika', 'seema', 'shaan',\n",
    "    'shiv', 'shivani', 'shruti', 'siddhant', 'simran', 'sneha', 'sonam', 'suhana',\n",
    "    'sumit', 'suraj', 'tanvi', 'tarun', 'tina', 'uday', 'varun', 'vedant',\n",
    "    'vibha', 'vidya', 'vikram', 'virat', 'vivek', 'yash', 'yashvi', 'zara',\n",
    "    'ansh', 'anushka', 'arnav', 'atharv', 'avantika', 'devansh', 'disha',\n",
    "    'gauri', 'himani', 'ishita', 'jiya', 'kartik', 'khushi', 'mahi', 'mainak',\n",
    "    'mitali', 'muskan', 'nandini', 'payal', 'prerna', 'riddhi', 'ritika',\n",
    "    'roshni', 'rujuta', 'rupa', 'rushil', 'sahana', 'saloni', 'shreya',\n",
    "    'siddhi', 'sriya', 'swara', 'tanya', 'tejal', 'trisha', 'urvi', 'veda'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Dataset: {len(NAMES)} names')\n",
    "print(f'Examples: {NAMES[:8]}')\n",
    "print(f'Average length: {np.mean([len(n) for n in NAMES]):.1f} characters')"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Part 1 — Tokenisation & Vocabulary\n",
    "\n",
    "We work at the **character level** — each character is one token.\n",
    "\n",
    "We add two special tokens:\n",
    "- `<S>` — Start of name\n",
    "- `<E>` — End of name"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Build character vocabulary\n",
    "all_chars = sorted(set(''.join(NAMES)))\n",
    "special   = ['<S>', '<E>']\n",
    "vocab     = special + all_chars\n",
    "char2idx  = {c: i for i, c in enumerate(vocab)}\n",
    "idx2char  = {i: c for c, i in char2idx.items()}\n",
    "VOCAB_SIZE = len(vocab)\n",
    "\n",
    "START_IDX = char2idx['<S>']\n",
    "END_IDX   = char2idx['<E>']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Vocabulary ({VOCAB_SIZE} tokens): {vocab}')\n",
    "print(f'<S> index: {START_IDX}, <E> index: {END_IDX}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build training examples: predict next character given current character\n",
    "# Context window = 1 (bigram model)\n",
    "# Format: (input_char_idx, target_char_idx)\n",
    "\n",
    "CONTEXT = 3  # use last 3 characters as context\n",
    "\n",
    "X_data = []  # list of context windows (each is a list of CONTEXT char indices)\n",
    "Y_data = []  # list of target char indices\n",
    "\n",
    "for name in NAMES:\n",
    "    # Pad with start tokens, end with end token\n",
    "    chars = [START_IDX] * CONTEXT + [char2idx[c] for c in name] + [END_IDX]\n",
    "    for i in range(CONTEXT, len(chars)):\n",
    "        context_window = chars[i - CONTEXT : i]\n",
    "        target = chars[i]\n",
    "        X_data.append(context_window)\n",
    "        Y_data.append(target)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_data = np.array(X_data)   # shape: (N, CONTEXT)\n",
    "Y_data = np.array(Y_data)   # shape: (N,)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nTraining examples: {len(X_data)}')\n",
    "print(f'Sample: context={[idx2char[i] for i in X_data[5]]}  →  target={idx2char[Y_data[5]]}')"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Part 2 — Embedding Layer\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of one-hot vectors (size 29), we map each character to a **learned dense embedding** (size 8).\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a simple lookup table: `embedding = C[char_idx]`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "EMBED_DIM = 8   # each character maps to an 8-dimensional vector\n",
    "\n",
    "# The embedding table C: shape (VOCAB_SIZE, EMBED_DIM)\n",
    "# Randomly initialised — will be learned during training\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "C = np.random.randn(VOCAB_SIZE, EMBED_DIM) * 0.1\n",
    "\n",
    "def embed(context_batch):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    context_batch: (batch, CONTEXT) integer indices\n",
    "    Returns: (batch, CONTEXT * EMBED_DIM) flattened embeddings\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Lookup embeddings for each character in context, then flatten\n",
    "    emb = C[context_batch]             # (batch, CONTEXT, EMBED_DIM)\n",
    "    return emb.reshape(len(context_batch), -1)  # (batch, CONTEXT*EMBED_DIM)\n",
    "\n",
    "INPUT_DIM = CONTEXT * EMBED_DIM   # 3 * 8 = 24\n",
    "print(f'Input to MLP: {INPUT_DIM} dimensions ({CONTEXT} chars × {EMBED_DIM} embedding dim)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test\n",
    "sample = X_data[:3]\n",
    "print(f'Sample embedding shape: {embed(sample).shape}')  # (3, 24)"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Part 3 — MLP from Scratch with NumPy\n",
    "\n",
    "We build a 2-layer MLP **manually** — no PyTorch here. You will implement:\n",
    "- Forward pass (linear → tanh → linear → softmax)\n",
    "- Cross-entropy loss\n",
    "- Backpropagation gradients\n",
    "- SGD update"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "def softmax(x):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Numerically stable softmax.\"\"\"\n",
    "    x = x - x.max(axis=1, keepdims=True)\n",
    "    e = np.exp(x)\n",
    "    return e / e.sum(axis=1, keepdims=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "def cross_entropy_loss(probs, targets):\n",
    "    \"\"\"probs: (batch, VOCAB_SIZE), targets: (batch,) int indices\"\"\"\n",
    "    N = len(targets)\n",
    "    correct_probs = probs[np.arange(N), targets]\n",
    "    return -np.log(correct_probs + 1e-8).mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ===== Network Parameters =====\n",
    "HIDDEN = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "# Layer 1: input → hidden\n",
    "W1 = np.random.randn(INPUT_DIM, HIDDEN) * 0.1\n",
    "b1 = np.zeros(HIDDEN)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Layer 2: hidden → output (vocab size)\n",
    "W2 = np.random.randn(HIDDEN, VOCAB_SIZE) * 0.1\n",
    "b2 = np.zeros(VOCAB_SIZE)\n",
    "\n",
    "# All learnable parameters (including embedding table C)\n",
    "params = [C, W1, b1, W2, b2]\n",
    "\n",
    "total = sum(p.size for p in params)\n",
    "print(f'Total parameters: {total}')\n",
    "print(f'  Embedding C:  {C.size}')\n",
    "print(f'  Layer 1 W1:   {W1.size}')\n",
    "print(f'  Layer 1 b1:   {b1.size}')\n",
    "print(f'  Layer 2 W2:   {W2.size}')\n",
    "print(f'  Layer 2 b2:   {b2.size}')"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "def forward(context_batch):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Full forward pass.\n",
    "    Returns: probs (batch, VOCAB_SIZE), and cache for backprop.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Embedding lookup + flatten\n",
    "    emb = embed(context_batch)           # (batch, INPUT_DIM)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Hidden layer\n",
    "    z1  = emb @ W1 + b1                  # (batch, HIDDEN)\n",
    "    h   = np.tanh(z1)                    # (batch, HIDDEN) — activation\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Output layer\n",
    "    z2    = h @ W2 + b2                  # (batch, VOCAB_SIZE)\n",
    "    probs = softmax(z2)                  # (batch, VOCAB_SIZE)\n",
    "\n",
    "    cache = (context_batch, emb, z1, h, z2, probs)\n",
    "    return probs, cache\n",
    "\n",
    "def backward(cache, targets, lr=0.1):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Backpropagation. Updates W1, b1, W2, b2, and C in-place.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    global C, W1, b1, W2, b2\n",
    "    context_batch, emb, z1, h, z2, probs = cache\n",
    "    N = len(targets)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Gradient of loss w.r.t. softmax output ---\n",
    "    # d_loss/d_z2 = probs - one_hot(targets)  [for cross-entropy + softmax]\n",
    "    dz2 = probs.copy()\n",
    "    dz2[np.arange(N), targets] -= 1\n",
    "    dz2 /= N\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Layer 2 gradients ---\n",
    "    dW2 = h.T @ dz2                      # (HIDDEN, VOCAB_SIZE)\n",
    "    db2 = dz2.sum(axis=0)               # (VOCAB_SIZE,)\n",
    "    dh  = dz2 @ W2.T                    # (batch, HIDDEN)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- tanh gradient ---\n",
    "    dz1 = dh * (1 - h**2)               # (batch, HIDDEN) — tanh derivative\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Layer 1 gradients ---\n",
    "    dW1  = emb.T @ dz1                  # (INPUT_DIM, HIDDEN)\n",
    "    db1  = dz1.sum(axis=0)              # (HIDDEN,)\n",
    "    demb = dz1 @ W1.T                   # (batch, INPUT_DIM)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- Embedding gradient ---\n",
    "    # Reshape demb back to (batch, CONTEXT, EMBED_DIM) and scatter-add into C\n",
    "    demb = demb.reshape(N, CONTEXT, EMBED_DIM)\n",
    "    dC   = np.zeros_like(C)\n",
    "    np.add.at(dC, context_batch, demb)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # --- SGD Updates ---\n",
    "    C  -= lr * dC\n",
    "    W1 -= lr * dW1\n",
    "    b1 -= lr * db1\n",
    "    W2 -= lr * dW2\n",
    "    b2 -= lr * db2\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Forward and backward pass defined.')"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# ===== Training Loop =====\n",
    "EPOCHS    = 200\n",
    "BATCH     = 32\n",
    "LR        = 0.1\n",
    "losses    = []\n",
    "\n",
    "N = len(X_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(EPOCHS):\n",
    "    # Shuffle data\n",
    "    idx   = np.random.permutation(N)\n",
    "    X_shf = X_data[idx]\n",
    "    Y_shf = Y_data[idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "    epoch_loss = 0\n",
    "    steps      = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i in range(0, N, BATCH):\n",
    "        Xb = X_shf[i:i+BATCH]\n",
    "        Yb = Y_shf[i:i+BATCH]\n",
    "\n",
    "        probs, cache = forward(Xb)\n",
    "        loss         = cross_entropy_loss(probs, Yb)\n",
    "        backward(cache, Yb, lr=LR)\n",
    "\n",
    "        epoch_loss += loss\n",
    "        steps      += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    avg_loss = epoch_loss / steps\n",
    "    losses.append(avg_loss)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if (epoch + 1) % 20 == 0:\n",
    "        print(f'Epoch {epoch+1:3d}/{EPOCHS}  Loss: {avg_loss:.4f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Learning rate decay\n",
    "    if epoch == 100:\n",
    "        LR = 0.01\n",
    "        print(f'  → LR decayed to {LR}')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
    "plt.plot(losses, color='darkorange', linewidth=2)\n",
    "plt.title('Training Loss', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Epoch'); plt.ylabel('Cross-Entropy Loss')\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Part 4 — Name Generation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "def generate_name(prefix='', max_len=15, temperature=0.8):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Generate a name character by character.\n",
    "    prefix: starting characters (e.g. 'Dhr')\n",
    "    temperature: > 1 = more random, < 1 = more greedy\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Initialise context with start tokens\n",
    "    context = [START_IDX] * CONTEXT\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Seed with prefix characters\n",
    "    prefix_lower = prefix.lower()\n",
    "    generated = list(prefix_lower)\n",
    "    for ch in prefix_lower:\n",
    "        if ch in char2idx:\n",
    "            context = context[1:] + [char2idx[ch]]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for _ in range(max_len):\n",
    "        ctx_arr = np.array([context])\n",
    "        probs, _ = forward(ctx_arr)\n",
    "        p = probs[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Temperature scaling\n",
    "        logits = np.log(p + 1e-8) / temperature\n",
    "        logits -= logits.max()\n",
    "        p = np.exp(logits)\n",
    "        p /= p.sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Sample next character\n",
    "        next_idx = np.random.choice(VOCAB_SIZE, p=p)\n",
    "\n",
    "        if next_idx == END_IDX:\n",
    "            break\n",
    "\n",
    "        next_char = idx2char[next_idx]\n",
    "        generated.append(next_char)\n",
    "        context = context[1:] + [next_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "    return ''.join(generated).capitalize()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# ===== Sanity Check =====\n",
    "print('========== SANITY CHECK ==========')\n",
    "final_probs, _ = forward(X_data)\n",
    "final_loss = cross_entropy_loss(final_probs, Y_data)\n",
    "print(f'Final training loss: {final_loss:.4f}')\n",
    "if final_loss < 2.5:\n",
    "    print('✅ PASS: Loss < 2.5 — model has learned something!')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('❌ Loss still high. Try training more epochs or adjusting learning rate.')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n===== GENERATED NAMES =====')\n",
    "print('\\nStarting with \"A\":')\n",
    "for _ in range(5):\n",
    "    print(f'  {generate_name(\"a\")}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nStarting with \"Dhr\":')\n",
    "for _ in range(5):\n",
    "    print(f'  {generate_name(\"dhr\")}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nFree generation (no prefix):')\n",
    "for _ in range(8):\n",
    "    print(f'  {generate_name()}')"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Bonus — Visualise Character Embeddings with PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "If your model learned good embeddings, similar characters (vowels, consonants) should cluster together in the embedding space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "# PCA to reduce 8-dim embeddings to 2-dim for visualisation\n",
    "# Only plot actual characters (not special tokens)\n",
    "char_indices = [char2idx[c] for c in all_chars]\n",
    "char_embs    = C[char_indices]\n",
    "\n",
    "pca   = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
    "emb2d = pca.fit_transform(char_embs)\n",
    "\n",
    "vowels     = set('aeiou')\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, ch in enumerate(all_chars):\n",
    "    color = '#e74c3c' if ch in vowels else '#3498db'\n",
    "    ax.scatter(emb2d[i, 0], emb2d[i, 1], color=color, s=100, zorder=5)\n",
    "    ax.annotate(ch, (emb2d[i, 0] + 0.01, emb2d[i, 1] + 0.01), fontsize=13)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.scatter([], [], color='#e74c3c', s=100, label='Vowels')\n",
    "ax.scatter([], [], color='#3498db', s=100, label='Consonants')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Character Embeddings (PCA 2D Projection)', fontsize=14, pad=12)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('PC 1'); ax.set_ylabel('PC 2')\n",
    "ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Do vowels cluster together? Do certain consonants group?')\n",
    "print('The more distinct the clusters, the more the model has learned about character relationships.')"
   ],
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": []
  },
